00:05:29.920 --> 00:05:31.990
Obviously, one of the
biggest problems in Africa

00:05:31.990 --> 00:05:37.210
today is elephant ivory.

00:05:37.210 --> 00:05:41.170
Elephant ivory is still
a widely traded product.

00:05:41.170 --> 00:05:43.360
An elephant is killed on
the continent of Africa

00:05:43.360 --> 00:05:46.570
roughly every 15 minutes,
and those are always

00:05:46.570 --> 00:05:48.250
killed for ivory.

00:05:48.250 --> 00:05:49.930
And the sad thing
is, it doesn't matter

00:05:49.930 --> 00:05:51.760
how big or old or
young the elephant

00:05:51.760 --> 00:05:55.510
is, if there's any ivory
at all, it will be taken.

00:05:55.510 --> 00:05:59.260
The good news is in
partnership, Wild Aid

00:05:59.260 --> 00:06:01.090
has sort of led
the fight on this,

00:06:01.090 --> 00:06:04.540
China has in the last year
banned the sale of ivory.

00:06:04.540 --> 00:06:06.190
Hong Kong has banned
the sale of ivory.

00:06:06.190 --> 00:06:08.530
Taiwan recently banned
the sale of ivory.

00:06:08.530 --> 00:06:11.230
Singapore is about to
ban the sale of ivory.

00:06:11.230 --> 00:06:12.670
So there is progress being made.

00:06:12.670 --> 00:06:15.490
The price of ivory
is dropping per kilo,

00:06:15.490 --> 00:06:18.910
but it's still an expensive
product that people buy.

00:06:18.910 --> 00:06:22.810
Japan, if you didn't know,
Japan is the last legal market

00:06:22.810 --> 00:06:24.830
for ivory left on the planet.

00:06:24.830 --> 00:06:26.810
And we're working hard
to shut that one down.

