00:07:31.400 --> 00:07:35.150
Rhinos, unfortunately rhinos is
another big problem in Africa.

00:07:35.150 --> 00:07:38.150
Rhino poaching for the horn.

00:07:38.150 --> 00:07:42.500
The horn is worth more by
weight than diamonds, gold,

00:07:42.500 --> 00:07:44.870
and cocaine.

00:07:44.870 --> 00:07:46.460
Currently, the
price of rhino horn

00:07:46.460 --> 00:07:49.970
is somewhere around
$15,000 to $20,000 a kilo.

00:07:49.970 --> 00:07:52.850
At its height, it
was $60,000 a kilo.

00:07:52.850 --> 00:07:56.700
So the good news is the price
of rhino horn is falling.

00:07:56.700 --> 00:07:59.960
But the bad news is
about three rhinos a day

00:07:59.960 --> 00:08:02.060
across the African
continent are poached

00:08:02.060 --> 00:08:04.130
for rhino horn, three a day.

00:08:04.130 --> 00:08:08.599
There's only about 25,000
rhinos left in the wild.

00:08:08.599 --> 00:08:09.390
So you do the math.

00:08:09.390 --> 00:08:12.090
In the last few years,
something like 6,000 rhinos

00:08:12.090 --> 00:08:13.260
have been poached.

00:08:13.260 --> 00:08:16.530
So if the current
trend is not reversed,

00:08:16.530 --> 00:08:19.800
rhinos could be extinct in the
wild in about 20 years, which

00:08:19.800 --> 00:08:21.900
is a sad thing.

00:08:21.900 --> 00:08:24.090
The rhino poaching
peaked in the '70s,

00:08:24.090 --> 00:08:26.400
and then went down in
the '80s, and early '90s.

00:08:26.400 --> 00:08:30.900
And then beginning in the 2000s,
a new market opened in Vietnam

00:08:30.900 --> 00:08:34.390
for rhino horn, and they were
claiming that it cured cancer,

00:08:34.390 --> 00:08:37.049
that it was an
aphrodisiac, that it

00:08:37.049 --> 00:08:39.780
did all these wonderful,
magical things.

00:08:39.780 --> 00:08:42.010
Rhino horn, for
your information,

00:08:42.010 --> 00:08:44.830
is made of the same thing
as your fingernail, keratin.

00:08:44.830 --> 00:08:46.290
So if you really
want rhino horn,

00:08:46.290 --> 00:08:48.330
just bite on your
fingernail or your toenail.

00:08:48.330 --> 00:08:50.650
There's more of it there.

00:08:50.650 --> 00:08:55.140
So what we try to do
is we try to discourage

00:08:55.140 --> 00:08:58.890
sales of rhino horn in Asia,
which is a difficult thing

00:08:58.890 --> 00:09:00.070
to do.

00:09:00.070 --> 00:09:03.030
There's a lot of solutions
people have proposed.

00:09:03.030 --> 00:09:06.150
Some conservancies
shave off the horn.

00:09:06.150 --> 00:09:08.760
Some conservancies
poison the horn.

00:09:08.760 --> 00:09:11.370
But this involves a
very expensive process

00:09:11.370 --> 00:09:15.180
of tranquilizing the animal
with a vet, bringing it in,

00:09:15.180 --> 00:09:18.840
and even with a horn
cut off a rhino,

00:09:18.840 --> 00:09:22.350
poachers will still kill the
rhino for the stump of horn,

00:09:22.350 --> 00:09:24.390
it's worth that much money.

00:09:24.390 --> 00:09:27.720
This rhino is named Najin.

00:09:27.720 --> 00:09:31.020
She is one of two
remaining Northern White

00:09:31.020 --> 00:09:33.280
Rhinos left on the planet.

00:09:33.280 --> 00:09:37.590
She and her pen mate, out of
the photo, are the only two

00:09:37.590 --> 00:09:39.660
of this species
left on the planet.

00:09:39.660 --> 00:09:41.056
The male died earlier this year.

00:09:41.056 --> 00:09:42.180
You may have read about it.

00:09:42.180 --> 00:09:43.900
His name was Sudan.

00:09:43.900 --> 00:09:46.580
I have a picture
of him coming up.

00:09:46.580 --> 00:09:49.320
She is too old to breed,
and so is her friend.

00:09:49.320 --> 00:09:53.970
